      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "As you noticed, the implementation already doesn't treat in/out as permissions.\r\n\r\nUsing `-whitelist` for both allows for easily specifying the same flags for both in,out. I can't think of any benefit to having separate options. (I'm not sure why we'd want to support different sets of flags...)",
